00:01:43,571 --> 00:01:44,851
=Light Beyond the Reed=

2
00:01:44,851 --> 00:01:47,410
(Adapted from the Jinjiang novel
"Light Beyond the Reed" by Mo Shubai)

3
00:01:48,220 --> 00:01:51,220
=Episode 12=

4
00:01:53,460 --> 00:01:54,980
Any plans after

5
00:01:54,980 --> 00:01:56,180
the case ends?

6
00:01:57,050 --> 00:01:58,050
Why do you ask?

7
00:01:59,490 --> 00:02:00,620
It'd be like a rebirth.

8
00:02:01,460 --> 00:02:02,300
Didn't you say

9
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:05,100
you wanted to do things that you wanted

10
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:06,620
but never got to do?

11
00:02:08,010 --> 00:02:08,940
I've thought about

12
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:10,940
whether I should stay at Nancheng

13
00:02:11,610 --> 00:02:13,100
or in other cities.

14
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,311
That would depend on Sibei.

15
00:02:18,220 --> 00:02:20,890
There's something
I've been curious about.

16
00:02:22,820 --> 00:02:23,660
If

17
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:25,660
you married someone else

18
00:02:26,130 --> 00:02:27,380
instead of Ye Sibei,

19
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:31,570
could you accept this?

20
00:02:34,010 --> 00:02:34,850
That's because

21
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:36,340
we've handled

22
00:02:36,340 --> 00:02:37,380
a similar case.

23
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:39,060
In the end,

24
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:40,130
they won the case,

25
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:41,222
but lost their marriage.

26
00:02:42,177 --> 00:02:43,466
That won't happen to us.

27
00:02:47,780 --> 00:02:49,730
You met through matchmaking, right?

28
00:02:51,111 --> 00:02:52,850
You've only been
married for a year or so,

29
00:02:53,730 --> 00:02:55,220
and your relationship is so strong.

30
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,010
You knew her before?

31
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,010
No.

32
00:02:58,660 --> 00:02:59,940
I didn't.

33
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:00,850
I'd never met her.

34
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:03,540
Really?

35
00:03:04,711 --> 00:03:06,010
Which school did you go to?

36
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:07,940
No. 7.

37
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:12,010
I guess not, then.

38
00:03:12,010 --> 00:03:14,170
I was wondering if you two

39
00:03:14,170 --> 00:03:16,290
were from the same school.

40
00:03:16,290 --> 00:03:18,730
You'd have something in common,

41
00:03:18,730 --> 00:03:20,220
or perhaps you'd met her before

42
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:21,410
but forgot about it.

43
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:22,466
But that's not the case.

44
00:03:23,290 --> 00:03:25,450
No. 2 and No. 7 High School

45
00:03:25,450 --> 00:03:26,980
are still pretty far apart.

46
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:34,820
Nan.

47
00:03:35,060 --> 00:03:35,900
Captain Zhang.

48
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,500
How is it, Nianwen?

49
00:03:38,555 --> 00:03:39,660
Everything going well?

50
00:03:46,866 --> 00:03:48,533
Chuchu has changed her testimony.

51
00:03:48,622 --> 00:03:50,820
She said she didn't
give my sister the condom,

52
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:52,200
implying that it was my sister's.

53
00:04:08,450 --> 00:04:09,610
Rise, everyone.

54
00:04:13,890 --> 00:04:14,890
The People's Court

55
00:04:14,890 --> 00:04:16,930
of Nancheng, Linjiang Province

56
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:18,340
(Defendant)
has reached a judgment.

57
00:04:26,490 --> 00:04:29,100
After deliberation by a collegial panel,

58
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,250
which is then submitted to
the Adjudication Committee

59
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,511
for discussion of a proceeding

60
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,850
initiated by the
Public Prosecution Service,

61
00:04:34,850 --> 00:04:35,810
the court finds that

62
00:04:35,810 --> 00:04:36,650
the evidence against

63
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:39,490
the defendant,
Fan Jiancheng, is insufficient.

64
00:04:39,490 --> 00:04:41,377
Therefore, the court finds the defendant

65
00:04:41,377 --> 00:04:42,220
not guilty of rape.

66
00:05:04,260 --> 00:05:05,100
(Presiding Judge)

67
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:10,220
Wenwen.

68
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,290
You saw that?

69
00:06:11,290 --> 00:06:13,020
Daddy has been acquitted.

70
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:13,780
He's a good person.

71
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:15,290
He was framed.

72
00:06:15,290 --> 00:06:17,140
He will be home soon to see you.

73
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:18,610
Yes, I'm innocent.

74
00:06:19,290 --> 00:06:20,660
I did nothing wrong.

75
00:06:21,540 --> 00:06:22,780
I want to thank the law

76
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:25,290
and the court for proving my innocence.

77
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:27,290
Of course, I must thank my wife

78
00:06:27,290 --> 00:06:28,111
for working so hard

79
00:06:28,133 --> 00:06:29,220
and staying by my side.

80
00:06:30,610 --> 00:06:32,020
As a father

81
00:06:33,020 --> 00:06:34,490
and a husband,

82
00:06:35,660 --> 00:06:38,410
I do have some imperfections.

83
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,780
I hope that my case will set
an example for everyone,

84
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:45,490
and I will be reflecting
deeply on my actions.

85
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:01,900
You scumbag!

86
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,170
What are you doing? Let go!

87
00:07:07,866 --> 00:07:09,410
Ye Sibei's family is assaulting him!

88
00:08:36,770 --> 00:08:37,770
Move!

89
00:08:37,770 --> 00:08:38,530
Let go!

90
00:08:38,530 --> 00:08:40,100
- Move!
- Let go of me!

91
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,130
What are you doing?

92
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:46,610
Get a hold of yourself!

93
00:08:46,770 --> 00:08:47,610
What are you doing?

94
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:48,820
Let go of me!

95
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:51,850
- Let go!
- Let go!

96
00:10:09,490 --> 00:10:10,420
That's enough.

97
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:11,530
Don't get upset over this.

98
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:14,180
I'm telling you, you're a cop.

99
00:10:14,490 --> 00:10:16,250
Don't get emotionally
involved in a case.

100
00:10:16,770 --> 00:10:17,940
Whatever you do,

101
00:10:18,155 --> 00:10:19,490
especially when handling a case,

102
00:10:19,770 --> 00:10:20,610
you...

103
00:10:22,010 --> 00:10:23,770
You can't let your emotions lead you.

104
00:10:23,770 --> 00:10:25,010
I know I'm a cop.

105
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:26,130
But, Captain Zhang.

106
00:10:27,820 --> 00:10:29,010
I'm also human.

107
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:32,460
Humans have a sense
of conscience, right?

108
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:43,010
Still, the court must have

109
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:46,490
their reason to deliver this verdict.

110
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:48,420
I understand.

111
00:10:52,130 --> 00:10:53,250
Before I left the courthouse,

112
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:55,250
I went to talk to Judge Gao.

113
00:10:59,220 --> 00:11:00,060
Judge Gao.

114
00:11:00,490 --> 00:11:01,060
Captain Zhang.

115
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:02,150
Thank you for your hard work.

116
00:11:02,155 --> 00:11:02,730
You too.

117
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:04,250
I have a question.

118
00:11:04,250 --> 00:11:05,610
Why did the court

119
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:06,820
find him not guilty?

120
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:09,300
I'm sorry.

121
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:12,010
I know it has been hard on Ye Sibei.

122
00:11:12,490 --> 00:11:14,820
It requires immense courage
to take this step.

123
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:16,580
However, as judges,

124
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:19,580
we can only deliberate our verdict

125
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,850
based on evidence and facts.

126
00:11:21,770 --> 00:11:23,130
We try our very best

127
00:11:23,666 --> 00:11:24,890
to ensure justice for all.

128
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:29,890
Let me tell you about a case from 1999.

129
00:11:31,010 --> 00:11:33,820
A woman accused a man of raping her.

130
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:36,820
While there were flaws
in the chain of evidence,

131
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:37,890
basically,

132
00:11:37,890 --> 00:11:40,010
it made sense
that the man was the culprit.

133
00:11:40,444 --> 00:11:41,730
Besides, we used to prioritize

134
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:42,940
statements and testimonies,

135
00:11:43,460 --> 00:11:45,580
and the woman wailed uncontrollably,

136
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:48,711
so the man was jailed for 12 years.

137
00:11:49,370 --> 00:11:52,250
When he was released 12 years later,
he kept appealing his case

138
00:11:52,890 --> 00:11:54,622
and spent many years doing so,

139
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:57,010
until a fugitive on the run

140
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:59,250
admitted that he was the true culprit.

141
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:01,610
That's how his innocence was restored.

142
00:12:02,770 --> 00:12:03,890
Who'd have expected

143
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:07,250
that things would turn out this way?

144
00:12:08,940 --> 00:12:09,780
Judge Gao.

145
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:12,180
He was jailed for 12 years,

146
00:12:13,266 --> 00:12:14,580
then spent years appealing.

147
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:17,010
Wouldn't you say he wasted

148
00:12:17,010 --> 00:12:19,010
most of his life on this case?

149
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,580
That's why we need to understand

150
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,730
that once the law is violated,

151
00:12:23,730 --> 00:12:25,770
whether it's an aggrieved victim

152
00:12:25,770 --> 00:12:27,730
or an innocent man maligned,

153
00:12:27,730 --> 00:12:29,180
it would be incredibly tormenting.

154
00:12:29,730 --> 00:12:31,180
What we can do

155
00:12:31,180 --> 00:12:33,130
is to prepare sufficient evidence

156
00:12:33,130 --> 00:12:36,010
to explore what's closest to the truth.

157
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:38,250
I believe you understand what I mean.

158
00:12:43,010 --> 00:12:44,730
It's tough being a judge.

159
00:12:50,890 --> 00:12:52,730
If you really care,

160
00:12:54,610 --> 00:12:56,010
keep investigating this case.

161
00:12:59,730 --> 00:13:00,610
This case

162
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:02,090
isn't over.

163
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:02,770
Wenwen!

164
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:07,890
Wenwen!

165
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:10,530
- Where's my daughter?
- Daddy!

166
00:14:10,530 --> 00:14:11,850
Daddy!

167
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:13,730
- Wenwen!
- I missed you.

168
00:14:13,730 --> 00:14:15,300
You're finally back.

169
00:14:16,420 --> 00:14:17,980
I missed you.

170
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:19,260
Let's hug it out.

171
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:20,820
And a kiss.

172
00:14:22,650 --> 00:14:23,700
Not enough.

173
00:14:25,650 --> 00:14:26,940
My daughter is getting

174
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:28,420
prettier by the day, isn't she?

175
00:14:30,850 --> 00:14:31,730
Daddy.

176
00:14:32,180 --> 00:14:35,490
They said you did something bad.

177
00:14:35,490 --> 00:14:36,840
Who said that?

178
00:14:36,850 --> 00:14:37,740
I'll slap them.

179
00:14:38,180 --> 00:14:39,360
I'm a good guy.

180
00:14:43,060 --> 00:14:44,980
More hugs from Daddy.

181
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:46,300
Take her to bed.

182
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:48,540
Go to bed.

183
00:14:48,770 --> 00:14:51,220
- I still want to play with Daddy.
- Go to bed.

184
00:14:52,060 --> 00:14:53,420
You can play tomorrow.

185
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:54,730
Daddy's back.

186
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:55,980
Wenwen!

187
00:14:55,980 --> 00:14:56,890
Now that I'm back,

188
00:14:56,890 --> 00:14:58,460
I can keep you company every day.

189
00:14:58,460 --> 00:14:59,980
Go to bed early,

190
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:01,850
and we can play all day tomorrow,

191
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:02,460
okay?

192
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:03,300
Okay.

193
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,580
Let me kiss my little princess.

194
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:07,300
- There.
- Go to bed.

195
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:09,250
Mommy.

196
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,400
Good night. Go to bed.

197
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,155
- Good night, Daddy and Mommy.
- Good night.

198
00:15:13,177 --> 00:15:14,000
Good night.

199
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:23,730
Darling,

200
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:25,100
you see...

201
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:26,180
Don't touch me!

202
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:33,660
You...

203
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,180
You put something so dirty

204
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:38,220
into my daughter's trophy.

205
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:39,733
What's wrong with you?

206
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:42,460
Mr. Fan has a message for you.

207
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,580
He asked you to polish

208
00:15:44,580 --> 00:15:46,100
Wenwen's trophy.

209
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:55,300
Do you know

210
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:57,700
that you're standing here now

211
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:58,540
because of me?

212
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,140
If not for me,

213
00:16:00,530 --> 00:16:02,100
you'd still be in jail now!

214
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:05,970
Yes.

215
00:16:09,730 --> 00:16:10,570
It's my fault.

216
00:16:12,730 --> 00:16:14,130
I'm sorry, Darling.

217
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:23,444
Thank you for doing me
such a huge favor.

218
00:16:25,130 --> 00:16:26,430
I promise that in the future,

219
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:29,100
I'll treat you and Wenwen well.

220
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,850
Everything in the house,

221
00:16:30,850 --> 00:16:31,850
the house, the car,

222
00:16:31,850 --> 00:16:33,420
my money, as long as you want them,

223
00:16:33,420 --> 00:16:34,530
they're all yours.

224
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,140
Don't be angry.

225
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:42,340
I let you come back

226
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:44,180
so that you can be a good father.

227
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:47,220
From now on,

228
00:16:47,980 --> 00:16:49,180
you're on your own.

229
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:55,660
So...

230
00:16:57,533 --> 00:16:58,570
About the USB drive...

231
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:03,140
The USB drive?

232
00:17:09,730 --> 00:17:10,570
You will never know

233
00:17:12,860 --> 00:17:14,980
where the USB drive is.

234
00:17:29,420 --> 00:17:31,050
(Headlines)
Please briefly tell us

235
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:32,180
what happened that day.

236
00:17:34,460 --> 00:17:36,570
That night, both of us drank alcohol.

237
00:17:36,570 --> 00:17:38,220
We went back home together.

238
00:17:38,220 --> 00:17:39,733
My house was just ten minutes away,

239
00:17:39,733 --> 00:17:40,730
so I got there first.

240
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:43,980
Before I left, I reminded her

241
00:17:44,622 --> 00:17:46,555
to send me a message
once she reached home.

242
00:17:48,050 --> 00:17:49,180
When you got down,

243
00:17:49,180 --> 00:17:51,220
was the victim in a clear state of mind?

244
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:55,420
We chatted in the car.

245
00:17:56,730 --> 00:17:57,730
(Both of us were)

246
00:17:58,810 --> 00:17:59,810
(a little tipsy,)

247
00:18:00,330 --> 00:18:01,860
(but still pretty much sane.)

248
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:03,330
(What did you chat about?)

249
00:18:04,220 --> 00:18:05,860
(She said life is too hard,)

250
00:18:06,980 --> 00:18:09,570
(and I told her to keep
moving forward regardless.)

251
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:10,570
That means

252
00:18:10,570 --> 00:18:12,530
you didn't abandon her.

253
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:19,290
Only both of us were in the car.

254
00:18:20,730 --> 00:18:22,420
Based on what you say,

255
00:18:22,420 --> 00:18:24,290
if I were the one who lived further,

256
00:18:24,290 --> 00:18:26,290
I'd have been the victim,

257
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:28,420
and she'd have been the one
who abandoned me, right?

258
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:31,420
You're saying that

259
00:18:31,980 --> 00:18:35,300
either of us could've been
at fault, right?

260
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:37,330
Did she send you a message

261
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:38,250
when she reached home?

262
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:45,140
All I can say is that
I made sure she was safe

263
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:46,140
before I slept.

264
00:18:46,711 --> 00:18:48,810
(I don't feel like answering
this question anymore.)

265
00:18:49,177 --> 00:18:50,420
(It's been said that the victim)

266
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,050
took a loan out

267
00:18:51,050 --> 00:18:53,220
to buy a house for you and her brother.

268
00:18:53,220 --> 00:18:54,730
Did you know about this before?

269
00:18:54,730 --> 00:18:55,570
No.

270
00:18:56,420 --> 00:18:57,380
Our families

271
00:18:57,380 --> 00:18:59,010
got together to discuss our marriage.

272
00:18:59,930 --> 00:19:01,420
At first, my father requested for

273
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:02,710
a bride price and a house.

274
00:19:03,230 --> 00:19:05,330
His family replied that they're not

275
00:19:05,330 --> 00:19:07,177
well off, and they
can't afford the bride price,

276
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,420
so they'll just buy us a house

277
00:19:08,420 --> 00:19:10,050
under my name and her brother's.

278
00:19:10,050 --> 00:19:11,533
Both of us would pay the house loan.

279
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:14,490
I always thought the down payment

280
00:19:14,490 --> 00:19:16,420
came from her brother's parents.

281
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:19,940
If I'd known Ye Sibei paid for it,

282
00:19:20,810 --> 00:19:21,980
I would've rejected.

283
00:19:25,580 --> 00:19:27,180
Now, because of this lawsuit,

284
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:30,380
we sold the house.

285
00:19:32,730 --> 00:19:33,900
From now on, I have...

